==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*hailaga-'' ‘holy, bringing health’, from ''*haila-'' ‘healthy’ (English [[whole]]).  Cognate with Old Saxon [[helag|hēlag]] (Dutch [[heilig]]), Old High German [[heilag]] (German [[heilig]]), Old Norse [[heilagr]] (Swedish [[helig]]), Gothic [[𐌷𐌰𐌹𐌻𐌰𐌲]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /ha:lɪj/

===Adjective===
'''hāliġ'''
